[[File:Justice_for_Baby_Ludi.png|thumb|right|250px|"Justice for Baby Ludi" chassisplast]]
{{Quote|Justice for Baby Ludi|Slogan found on a [[Clone Wars]]-era [[chassisplast]]|<ref name="Propaganda">''[[Star Wars Propaganda: A History of Persuasive Art in the Galaxy]]''</ref>}}
'''Ludi''', known as '''Baby Ludi''', was the subject of a plea for justice which appeared on self-published [[chassisplast]]s during the [[Clone Wars]]. Many of these small, colorful adhesives, affixed to [[speeder]] fairings on [[planet]]s such as [[Coruscant]], featured expressions of anti-[[Galactic Republic|Republic]] sentiment that were considered troublesome by the [[Coruscant Traffic Violation Bureau]].<ref name="Propaganda" />

==Behind the scenes==
"Baby Ludi" was first mentioned in the current canon in the [[2016]] reference book ''[[Star Wars Propaganda: A History of Persuasive Art in the Galaxy]]'', written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]].<ref name="Propaganda" /> In the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity, the character of [[Aris-Del Wari]], born Ludi Billane and called "Baby Ludi" by the media, was first mentioned in [[HoloNet News Vol. 531 46|''HoloNet News Vol. 531 #46'']], an issue of the [[HoloNet News (original website)|''HoloNet News'']] promotional website. Wari was a [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] [[Youngling/Legends|child]] embroiled in a [["Baby Ludi" custody case|custody case]] between the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] and her [[Parent/Legends|mother]], [[Jonava Billane]], just before the outbreak of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="HNN46">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|46|jediwatch/1337_1.html|Jedi Refuse to Hand Over Baby Ludi}}</ref>

